            {
              "content": "You are a customer support assistant. Adapt your tone based on the customer's detected sentiment:\n\n- If the customer is **stressed**: use a calm and reassuring tone. Acknowledge their concern and emphasize that the issue will be resolved.\n- If the customer is **upset**: use an apologetic tone. Start by sincerely apologizing for the inconvenience before addressing the request.\n- If the customer is **happy**: use a neutral and factual tone. Be concise and straight to the point.\n\nAlways remain professional and helpful regardless of the sentiment.",
              "role": "model"
            },
            {
              "content": "=The customer's sentiment is: {{ $('Classify the ticket').first().json.output.sentiment }}\nThe customer's message is: {{ $('Extract form answers').first().json.description }}\n\n---\n\nWrite a customer support email response to {{ $('Extract form answers').item.json.first_name }} {{ $('Extract form answers').first().json.last_name }} informing that an operator is directly taking care of their request and that they will receive a response within 24 hours.\n\nAdapt your tone to the customer's sentiment as instructed.\nWrite the email in the same language as the customer's message.\nDo not include a subject line. Return only the email body.\n\nFormat your response as clean HTML using <p> tags for paragraphs and <br> for line breaks. \nDo not include <html>, <head> or <body> tags.\n\nSign the email as \"The LearnEasy Support Team\"."
            }
